### Method Overloading in C#

Method overloading allows multiple methods with the same name but different parameters within the same class.

### Rules for Overloading

Methods must differ in:

- Number of parameters
- Type of parameters
- Order of parameters

Return type alone is NOT sufficient for overloading.

### Examples

```csharp
// Different number of parameters
static int Sum(int a, int b) => a + b;
static int Sum(int a, int b, int c) => a + b + c;

// Different types
static int Sum(int a, int b) => a + b;
static double Sum(double a, double b) => a + b;

// Different order
static void Display(string name, int age) { }
static void Display(int id, string name) { }
```

### Invalid Overloading

```csharp
// INVALID - only return type differs
static int Calculate(int x) { return x; }
static double Calculate(int x) { return x; }  // Error

// INVALID - same signature, different parameter name
static void Print(int value) { }
static void Print(int number) { }  // Error
```

### Overloading and Type Promotion

```csharp
static void Show(int x) => Console.WriteLine($"int: {x}");
static void Show(double x) => Console.WriteLine($"double: {x}");

Show(5);       // Calls Show(int)
Show(5.0);     // Calls Show(double)
Show(5f);      // Calls Show(double) after float->double
```

### Overloading Constructors

```csharp
class Person
{
    public string Name { get; set; }
    public int Age { get; set; }

    public Person() : this("Unknown", 0) { }
    public Person(string name) : this(name, 0) { }
    public Person(string name, int age)
    {
        Name = name;
        Age = age;
    }
}
```

### Overloading with Nullable Parameters

```csharp
static void Process(int value) { }
static void Process(int? value) { }  // Valid overload
```

### Benefits of Overloading

| Benefit | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| Readability | Same logical operation, same name |
| Consistency | Similar behavior across different types |
| API design | Flexible method signatures |
| Optional behavior | Defaults without optional parameters |

> **Key Point:** Overloading is about compile-time method resolution. The compiler selects the best match based on arguments. Return type cannot be used to distinguish overloads. Use overloading to provide different ways to call the same logical operation.

### Generic Overloading

```csharp
static void Process<T>(T value) { }
static void Process(string value) { }  // More specific match for strings
```

